  "text": "The composite primary endpoint \"gastrointestinal complications\" will be assessed from the date of pancreatoduodenectomy up to the end of the study on POD 30. Outcome observers will assess the presence of the primary endpoint during clinical visits and from the patients' files and by a telephone call on POD 30. If at least one item is assessed as present, the primary endpoint will have been reached for this patient. The severity of each complication will be classified by consensus and according to the Clavien-Dindo classification [CITATION_1] . If no consensus definition can be reached, the severity will be assessed according to the Clavien-Dindo classification only.",
